## Prerequisites

This block requires the **Custom Fields module** (`@mercurjs/core-plugin/modules/custom-fields`). Make sure it is registered in your `medusa-config.ts`.

## Configuration

Add request-related custom fields to the entities you want to support approval workflows for. Product already has a built-in `status` field, so you only need to configure custom fields for other entities.

Add these fields to your Custom Fields module options in `medusa-config.ts`:

```ts
{
  resolve: "@mercurjs/core-plugin/modules/custom-fields",
  options: {
    customFields: {
      ProductCollection: {
        request_status: {
          type: "enum",
          enum: ["draft", "pending", "accepted", "rejected"],
          defaultValue: "draft",
        },
        submitter_id: { type: "string", nullable: true },
        reviewer_id: { type: "string", nullable: true },
        reviewer_note: { type: "text", nullable: true },
      },
      // Add the same fields to other entities as needed:
      // ProductCategory, ProductType, ProductTag
    },
  },
}
```

## Middlewares

Add the request middlewares to your `api/middlewares.ts`:

```ts
import { defineMiddlewares } from "@medusajs/medusa";
import { adminRequestsMiddlewares } from "./admin/requests/middlewares";
import { vendorProductCollectionRequestsMiddlewares } from "./vendor/product-collections/middlewares";
import { vendorProductCategoryRequestsMiddlewares } from "./vendor/product-categories/middlewares";
import { vendorProductTypeRequestsMiddlewares } from "./vendor/product-types/middlewares";
import { vendorProductTagRequestsMiddlewares } from "./vendor/product-tags/middlewares";

export default defineMiddlewares({
  routes: [
    ...adminRequestsMiddlewares,
    ...vendorProductCollectionRequestsMiddlewares,
    ...vendorProductCategoryRequestsMiddlewares,
    ...vendorProductTypeRequestsMiddlewares,
    ...vendorProductTagRequestsMiddlewares,
  ],
});
```

If you already have a `middlewares.ts` file, merge the middleware imports and spread them into your existing `routes` array.

## Database Migrations

After updating the custom fields configuration, run migrations:

```bash
npx medusa db:migrate
```

## Run codegen

After installing the block, regenerate SDK types:

```bash
npx @mercurjs/cli@canary codegen
```

## API Endpoints

### Admin

- `GET /admin/requests/:type` — List entities with request custom fields (filterable by `request_status`, `submitter_id`)
- `GET /admin/requests/:type/:id` — Retrieve entity with request custom fields
- `POST /admin/requests/:type/:id/accept` — Accept a request
- `POST /admin/requests/:type/:id/reject` — Reject a request

Supported `:type` values: `product_collection`, `product_category`, `product_type`, `product_tag`

### Vendor

- `GET /vendor/product-collections` — List vendor's collection requests
- `POST /vendor/product-collections` — Create a collection request
- `GET /vendor/product-categories` — List vendor's category requests
- `POST /vendor/product-categories` — Create a category request
- `GET /vendor/product-types` — List vendor's type requests
- `POST /vendor/product-types` — Create a type request
- `GET /vendor/product-tags` — List vendor's tag requests
- `POST /vendor/product-tags` — Create a tag request

